transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hey, thanks for calling Viagra. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, I just got a notification from my bank that I guess my order just refilled again.

Speaker 1: And I need to put it on hold or something because I've got two complete orders in front of me already.

Speaker 2: It's Elwood, E-L-W-O-O-D.

Speaker 1: And your first name?

Speaker 2: Ralph, R-A-L-P-H.

Speaker 1: Let me see if it's gone, Ralph. Okay, I see here. I don't think it's gone out yet. I should be able to stop this.

Speaker 2: You just wanted to put a pause? Yeah, put a pause on the account. Whenever you're ready, you can give us a call.

Speaker 1: Okay, that would be good because I've got two full ones right here still.

Speaker 2: Okay, yeah, no worries.

Speaker 1: But I'll still be in the system?

Speaker 2: Yeah, yeah, you can give us a call. Just give us a shout when you're ready and we'll take care of it for you.

Speaker 1: Okay, I appreciate it. Thank you very much.

Speaker 2: No problem, and you're all set then, Mr. Elwood. Thank you.

Speaker 1: Thank you. Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye now.
